    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24776: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Governor of California</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stephens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sacramento</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 5:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Several United States Governors are invited to inaugural ceremonies of President
                    Obregón of Mexico. Does State Department advise trip being made? Kindly advise
                    at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. D. Stephens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
